flowRoot.flowPara: Quick connect permits logging into a new device without entering a password.
Using an already logged-in Jellyfin client, navigate to the settings to enter the quick connect code displayed above.

The server browsing view has a shared header bar
to allow for smooth transitions between its contents.
Its pages therefore don't have a header bar.
The disconnect and back buttons are each in a stack page,
the appropriate one is shown depending on the context.
Search and path bars are in a stack switcher.
The path bar is shown for item views
The search bar is shown when the search button
Navigation is shown in a navigation sidebar. Its toggle
button is on the left and is always visible. The navigation
items change the view stack to the appropriate view,
The preferences button is always shown.
The search button is toggleable and always shown.
The filter button is shown for collection views

flowRoot.flowPara: Disconnecting without logging out preserves the user session and avoids having to authenticate later.

text.tspan: In the season, show and movie views,
the thumbnail can be vertical or horizontal.
Episode and season cards may contain more text,
which is why they adopt the card model.
On the other hand, "root" cards (library, show, movie)
have their text on a downward extension of the poster.
